law.text:
A fiscal court, by ordinance, may assess additional fees and costs for the purpose of paying expenses for courthouses, bonds related to them, and administration expenses of the District Court as follows:
In all traffic offense cases, a fee of ten dollars ($10) may be added to the court costs;
In probate cases, a filing fee of ten dollars ($10) may be added to each filing fee;
In misdemeanor cases, a cost of twenty dollars ($20) may be added to the court costs;
In small claim cases, a fee of ten dollars ($10) may be added to all filing fees; and
In civil cases, a fee of ten dollars ($10) may be added to all filing fees.
